						               													<description>Kotu Elima originates from Sri Lanka and is (in similar versions) also played in India and Indonesia. The &amp;quot;Leopard Game&amp;quot; is a so called South Asian Siege Game. 2 leopards attack 24 cows.  For this reason it is well-known also under the name of &amp;quot;Cows and Leopards&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2 strategy games on one board:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Kotu Elima:  Each player has 24 marbles. Goal is it to strike the opposing stones by jumping over them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Leopard Game:  First the marbles are set, then alternating one player pulls.  The cows win, if the leopards cannot pull any longer, the leopards win, if they struck 8 cows.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
